    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are a job relevance scorer.\n\nCandidate Resume:\n\n{{ $('Resume Information').first().json.Resume }}\n\nBelow are jobs to evaluate:\n\n{{ JSON.stringify($json) }}\n\nFor each job, return:\n\n[\n{\n\"job_id\": \"\",\n\"title\": \"\",\n\"company\": \"\",\n\"location\": \"\",\n\"job_url\": \"\",\n\"score\": 0,\n\"reason\": \"\"\n}\n]\n\nScoring Criteria:\n\n* Role Match (30 points)\n* Skills Match (40 points)\n* Experience Match (15 points)\n* Location Match (10 points)\n* Bonus (5 points)\n\nScore Guidelines:\n\n* 90-100 = Exceptional fit\n* 80-89 = Strong fit\n* 70-79 = Possible fit\n* Below 70 = Not worth applying\n\nIMPORTANT RULES:\n\n1. You MUST return exactly one result for every input job.\n2. If 10 jobs are provided, return exactly 10 JSON objects.\n3. Do not skip any job even if relevance is low.\n4. Preserve the exact values of:\n\n   * job_id\n   * title\n   * company\n   * location\n   * job_url\n5. Do NOT modify, shorten, rewrite, or generate a new job_url.\n6. Copy the job_url exactly as it appears in the input.\n7. Return ONLY valid JSON.\n8. Do not include markdown, explanations, or code fences.\n\nReturn ONLY a JSON array.\n",
        "batching": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
      "typeVersion": 1.9,
      "position": [
        192,
